<TEXT>
young marriages face tough odds but 
todd and bonnie longsine seemed off to a good start and headed away 
from some of the troubles of their adolescent years 
the two teenagers owned a threebedroom mobile home a car and 
a pickup truck and had a happy 14monthold son josh whose blond 
hair and blue eyes charmed their friends 
but longsine 19 turned against his family this week fatally 
shooting 18yearold bonnie setting a fire that killed josh and 
then ending his own life their bodies were found thursday by a 
repairman making a service call to their trailer 
no suicide note was found leaving their neighbors in the 
country estates mobile home park in greenville a town of 225 in 
northeastern wisconsin without explanations 
from what i could tell from todd and bonnie everything seemed 
to be fine neighbor kathy nichols said it seemed like he had 
it together he was happy to be a father 
the couple married in october 1988 a month or so before josh 
was born and bought their trailer home a year later todd 
graduated from menasha high school in 1988 worked at a warehouse 
for a brief time and then enrolled in a trade school to learn metal 
welding bonnie was a waitress in nearby appleton hoping to move 
up to management 
their actions seemed to be cutting a path away from their rocky 
adolescence when todd had some skirmishes with the law and bonnie 
dropped out of menasha high before her junior year 
but not everybody believed that all was well with the couple 
wendy reiland a friend of mrs longsines said the young 
mother wanted out within months of the marriage then changed her 
mind the couple filed a joint divorce petition a year ago then 
withdrew it last summer 
a neighbor krista vollmer saw a for sale sign in the 
window of their trailer one day earlier this month officials at 
fox valley technical college said todd failed to register jan 19 
for the spring semester 
outagamie county sheriff thomas drootsan said the 22caliber 
rifle that longsine used was bought just this week he shot bonnie 
set the fire outside joshs bedroom that asphyxiated the toddler as 
he slept and then shot himself authorities said the deaths went 
undetected until the repairmans call thursday because the fire 
burned itself out 
sheriffs capt gary barrington said friday that longsine had a 
juvenile record including an arrest for disorderly conduct but 
had not been in major trouble there were no reports of wife or 
child abuse during the marriage authorities said 
i wish we had a real good motive to lay on you but right now 
we dont barrington said 
longsines stepgrandmother irene stoeger said she remembered 
her grandsons being in trouble while growing up his mother 
reported him to the police department a lot ms stoeger said 
quite a few years ago todd went on a rampage he got mad 
police in menasha said they investigated longsine to see if he 
was helping bonnie hide when she ran away from home in spring 1988 
at age 17 he was not charged with anything and she eventually came 
back home 
mrs longsines mother barb godeck said friday that the family 
had reservations about longsine when the two married later that 
year the couple had met at a dance she said 
there were probably a lot of things we werent pleased 
about she said sometimes you think you know someone and you 
really dont 
bonnie was a very loving person her mother added anyone 
who knew her liked her she had no enemies 
mrs longsines boss at marcs big boy restaurant dave 
anderson called her a hard worker he said she seemed quieter 
somewhat tense the last two weeks 
we had ideas she was having marriage problems but to what 
extent everybody goes through marriage problems he said as 
far as we knew they were doing ok financially 
</TEXT>
