<TEXT>
former first lady betty ford honored 
former white house press secretary james brady his wife sarah 
and a second couple for using their experiences with adversity to 
help others 
mrs ford on friday presented the bradys and kirk and karen ball 
of aurora with the first betty ford awards at a ceremony in beaver 
creek where mrs ford and former president gerald ford own a home 
it is gratifying to be involved with an award that recognizes 
the inner strength of individuals and their selflessness in aiding 
others said mrs ford whose betty ford center in rancho mirage 
calif treats chemical dependency 
the bradys were honored for their efforts to gain passage of 
national handgun control legislation james brady 49 was shot in 
the head during an assassination attempt on president reagan in 
1981 brady remains partially paralyzed 
mrs brady is vice chairman of handgun control inc a citizens 
group that lobbies for passage of federal legislation to place 
tighter controls on handguns 
kirk ball 31 and his wife karen 32 have a 4yearold 
daughter kaelin who was born with a portwine stain on both sides 
of her face doctors told the balls the stain is a symptom of a 
rare progressive disease known as sturgeweber syndrome other 
symptoms include eye problems seizures partial paralysis and even 
mental retardation 
they started the sturgeweber foundation to help other parents 
learn more about the disease and to encourage research the 
foundation now has more than 300 members worldwide 
</TEXT>
