<TEXT>
president bush is proposing 3033 billion for 
defense in a new budget that would increase spending for the 
strategic defense initiative and calls for five b2 stealth 
bombers say congressional sources and pentagon documents 
the budget plan to be released formally on monday also would 
cut military personnel by 38000 fund two landbased nuclear 
missiles and cancel a number of weapons programs including another 
attempt to scrap the marine corps v22 osprey aircraft 
the plan would add 7 billion to the military budget bringing 
it to 3033 billion for the 1991 fiscal year a 24 percent 
increase from this years 2963 billion but about 2 percent less 
than what the pentagon would need to keep pace with inflation 
the figure includes 2921 billion for pentagon spending up 
from 2868 billion with the rest representing energy department 
spending for nuclear programs according to documents made 
available to the associated press friday by congressional sources 
total budget authority for the military in the year beginning 
oct 1 would be 3069 billion up from 3016 billion also 
including energy department money 
the budget figures come amid dramatic changes in eastern europe 
where nations are pushing towards democracy and administration 
officials concede the soviet threat has lessened 
this budget represents the first steps in responding to 
changes in eastern europe and the soviet union as well as tighter 
budget constraints defense secretary dick cheney said in 
comments included in the documents 
the budget total for sdi commonly known as star wars is 45 
billion in pentagon spending adding approximately 300 million in 
energy department money the program would get 48 billion 
the total is a 1 billion increase over what congress approved 
last year and reflects strong support for a vigorous sdi program 
that includes the brilliant pebbles technology for spacebased 
interceptors the pentagon said 
brilliant pebbles is a system composed of many small ground and 
spacebased interceptors that would sense enemy ballistic missiles 
the interceptors would ram the missiles causing them to explode 
a number of democrats in congress question the system and favor 
longterm research on directed energy weapons 
the budget proposal also includes 55 billion for five b2 
bombers the radarevading batwinged aircraft that has come under 
attack on capitol hill for its high price of about 530 million 
apiece last year congress gave the bush administration two of the 
three bombers it sought and this years total of five is certain to 
be attacked 
another thorny issue is the administrations plan to fund two 
landbased nuclear missiles the singledwarhead midgetman and the 
multiplewarhead mx missile the budget proposal calls for 202 
million for the midgetman and 28 billion for the mx 
among the other highpriced strategic programs in the budget is 
15 billion for one trident submarine and 17 billion for 52 
trident ii nuclear missiles 
the budget also includes plans to mothball two battleships the 
uss new jersey and the uss iowa and cancellations of various 
weapons programs some of which were on the chopping block last 
year 
among the programs terminated are the marine corps v22 osprey 
tiltrotor aircraft the navys f14d jet fighter the phoenix and 
maverick missiles the apache helicopter the army helicopter 
improvement program ahip the f15e fighter and the m1 tank 
congress last year rejected the administrations attempt to 
eliminate the osprey 
the budget calls for a reduction in active troop strength by 
38000 from nearly 21 million and cuts in civilian forces of 5000 
and reserves by 3000 
at the pentagon a senior administration official said the 
spending would represent a decline in purchasing power after 
inflation is taken into account 
it means that we will be able to buy fewer planes tanks and 
ships and support fewer troops said the official who spoke 
only on condition he not be named 
