<DOCNO> AP900127-0026 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap haitis military ruler lt gen 
prosper avril says he is lifting a 30day state of siege under 
which security forces rounded up dozens of political activists and 
forced at least seven into exile 
in a speech friday night carried live on state radio and 
television avril said the state of siege would be withdrawn 
tuesday 18 days early in view of the positive results already 
obtained 
it was unclear whether avril was bowing to diplomatic pressure 
or simply felt he had effectively stifled open opposition to his 
16monthold regime 
the announcement came the same day the french government said it 
was suspending economic assistance and talks on a 500 million aid 
package for haiti one of the worlds poorest nations to protest 
avrils crackdown on his political opponents 
the 12nation european economic community also issued a strongly 
worded protest friday 
avril has also been under pressure from the bush administration 
which denounced the state of siege as a blatant assault on basic 
civil liberties the united states suspended 60 milion in annual 
direct aid to haiti after an election massacre in 1987 
in his speech avril did not say whether the seven exiled 
opposition leaders would be allowed to return however the 
interior and defense minister brig gen fritz romulus said 
earlier in the week that the seven could take part in elections 
scheduled for next fall 
avril also did not say whether censorship imposed on independent 
radio and television stations would be lifted along with the siege 
declaration 
the military leader wearing his uniform and sitting at his desk 
at the national palace addressed the nation before the start of 
the 10 pm news on state tv he read from a prepared text in 
french rather than creole the language of 90 percent of haitis 
57 million people 
the state of siege was imposed on jan 20 one day after 
unidentified gunmen killed army col andre neptune his wife and 
their housemaid 
avril who attended neptunes funeral friday blamed the 
assassination on unspecified terrorists and anarchists in 
apparent reference to the exiled opposition leaders avril said 
political demagogues had helped create a climate of insecurity 
in the country 
among the politicians forced into exile were dr louis roy one 
of the main authors of the 1987 constitution and hubert de 
ronceray a prominent conservative and former presidential 
candidate 
they were among an estimated 50 activists arrested and 
reportedly beaten in the military sweep last weekend 
although he did not acknowledge mistreatment by the military 
avril said the furor of the soldiers after neptunes killing 
was understandable 
he said the security forces had been hamstrung by certain 
constitutional guarantees such as a 48hour limit on holding 
suspects without bringing charges 
extraordinary measures were necessary avril said to 
safeguard our young tottering stammering democracy 
critics have accused avril of using the colonels assassination 
as a pretext to suppress opposition and renege on his pledge to 
turn over power to a democratically elected government elections 
are scheduled for oct 28 
but avril reiterated his pledge to hold elections 
the democratic process will not be put into question he 
said on the contrary in a more serene climate the electoral 
machine will advance more securely 
avril gained power in september 1988 when a soldiers rebellion 
ousted lt gen henri namphy who took over after a popular 
uprising forced dictator jeanclaude duvalier to flee to france in 
february 1986 
the last time haiti attempted free elections in november 1987 
armed thugs in collusion with government troops shot or hacked to 
death at least 34 voters and the balloting was canceled 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

