after waiting more than a year william 
and aleta heidt were ecstatic to learn last week that their plans 
to adopt two children from colombia had finally been approved 
but the joyous anticipation turned into hours of hellish 
desperation for mrs heidt when avianca flight 52 crashed with her 
husband and new son and daughter aboard 
mrs heidt of wyckoff nj went to john f kennedy 
international airport on thursday night carrying two small parkas 
blue and purple for her new children and a camera to take their 
pictures 
the adoptions had taken more than a year to set up and she knew 
her son and daughter blanca beltron 12 and her brother pedro 
10 only from a snapshot 
but avianca flight 52 never arrived and friday morning after a 
