sound relationship between the union and the transport service 
however the conservative partys transport spokesman jurg 
prinsloo said it is shocking that after one of the most violent 
strikes the strikers have again been installed in their 
posts 
the walkout was illegal under legislation that bars strikes in 
essential services the transport company employs about 170000 
people and runs rail and harbor operations nationwide 
