the trial opened one day after the vice president of the 
provisional government resigned claiming that stalinistic 
methods are being used by the nations new leaders 
those on trial include former party secretary emil bobu no 3 
under ceausescu and his wife elena former interior minister tudor 
postelnicu who headed the hated secret police and expolitburo 
members manea manescu and dinca if convicted they could receive 
20year prison sentences 
the four sat together in a box in the courtroom with two 
uniformed guards behind them the trial began with each of the 
defendants asked to list his age background and education the 
charges were then read as the four defendants listened impassively 
then the questioning began 
the charges referred to ceausescu and his wife as the 
authors of the genocide but said the four defendants did not 
act to block the ceausescus from taking illegal actions and 
therefore were guilty of complicity 
the ceausescus were found guilty of grave crimes and 
executed dec 25 among those charges was genocide which officials 
said referred to 60000 people slain during the communist 
dictators regime 
the defendants were not asked at first to plead to the charges 
but were questioned about events leading to orders for the security 
forces to open fire on unarmed demonstrators during the revolution 
the order was given by ceausescu at a meeting of the political 
executive committee of the communist party or politburo on dec 
17 while demonstrators in the western city of timisoara were 
demanding the dictators ouster 
dinca said ceausescu wanted soldiers to fire in the air over the 
heads of demonstrators and at the legs of those who broke into 
stores party headquarters or other institutions 
he said ceausescu then asked if those at the meeting had other 
opinions 
nobody had any other opinions dinca recalled 
he did not make clear how the orders were expanded to shots 
fired at the heads and bodies of demonstrators but accepted 
responsibility for what he called criminal measures 
i gave my help to ceausescu to put into practice the criminal 
measures to suffocate in blood the justified revolution of the 
people he said 
when asked why the revolution was justified dinca said the 
people suffered a lack of constitutional rights human freedom 
a lack of food and medication 
the charge was read out as falling under the section of the 
romanian penal code that says genocide constitutes the action of 
destroying a nation a community or an ethnic group by murder 
western diplomats in bucharest citing witness accounts and 
their own assessments believe 10000 people died in the uprising 
when he resigned friday vice president dumitru mazilu said 
stalinist methods and practices are still being used by the 
provisional government and the press is still directed to destroy 
some people and promote others 
i am convinced that those who have carried out the revolution 
will never accept that it be taken over by people who havent given 
anything of themselves to it he said after reading his 
resignation on radio free europe 
</TEXT>
