security plan would turn beirut into an oasis of peace 
hrawi leads a christianmoslem government that is backed by 
syria which has the largest military presence in lebanon 
christian gen michel aoun whose forces control the christian 
enclave refuses to recognize the government and has vowed to drive 
the syrians from lebanon 
the security plan according to government sources is to be put 
into effect early next week 
one source speaking on condition of anonymity said the plan 
calls for troops loyal to hrawis government and lebanese police to 
join and then replace syrian troops in most of west beirut 
no lebanese or syrian forces will deploy in the heart of south 
beiruts slums where underground proiranian factions holding most 
of the 18 western hostages in lebanon are based the source said 
