resettlers can expect a wait of up to three years in temporary 
quarters before they move into permanent lodgings 
but west germanys prosperous economy offers them greater 
prospects than in east germany and while theyre adjusting to 
their new surroundings the resettlers are cradled by bonns social 
welfare net 
east germans resettlers are automatically given 200 marks 118 
in bridgingover money when they arrive in west germany 
they also are eligible for the same state pensions as west 
germans 
in addition an unemployed resettler can collect integration 
money of 647 a month for one year according to the west german 
interior ministry 
that may not sound like much but its higher than the average 
monthly east german salary of about 530 and compares to an 
average monthly salary of 1882 in west germany 
many west germans still resent the expenditure of their 
hardearned tax money on those flooding in from the east 
