<TEXT>
budget director richard g darman will liken 
the federal budget to a voracious cookie monster in a fanciful 
message to congress that also will warn lawmakers against expecting 
a peace dividend from reduced tensions in eastern europe 
the budget for all its intimidating detail might be seen 
as the ultimate cookie monster darman will assert in an 
introduction to bushs 12 trillion fiscal 1991 budget 
its excess tendencies toward consumption are not exactly 
ennobling but at the same time its underlying motivation is 
clearly not malevolent what harm it might cause is largely 
unintended darman writes 
darman in the introduction to be formally released with the 
budget on monday tells congress that the job of responsible public 
officials is to seek to get the cookie monster under control 
darman also will caution lawmakers against seeking a 
wonderland in which military savings can be diverted to 
domestic programs 
the nearterm peace dividend is likely to be smaller than 
commonly assumed darman says in his introduction 
some members of congress have proposed that the reductions in 
military tensions in eastern europe can be turned into a socalled 
peace dividend and spent on expanding social programs 
darman however tells congress it would be naively euphoric 
to expect that the crumbling of the soviet empire will spell a 
final end to eastwest tensions 
still bushs budget will propose an austere 2921 billion in 
pentagon spending for the fiscal year that begins next oct 1 
representing the lowest increase in more than a decade and an 
actual reduction of about 2 percent if inflation is taken into 
account according to administration sources 
excerpts from darmans introduction were first published in 
saturdays editions of the new york times and later confirmed by 
administration officials 
darman asserts that the great historical shift in eastern 
europe has been almost trivialized in its translation into public 
debate about the budget the issue has been framed as how big is 
the peace dividend and in effect how can i get mine 
he said the prime objective of the budget was not to find other 
ways of spending military savings but how can it best preserve 
and build on americas strengths 
darman asks in his partly whimsical introduction how big is 
the deficit and paraphrasing elizabeth barrett browning he 
answers the question let me count the ways 
darman also will tell congress that many programs in the budget 
are like the hungry monsters in pac man the popular video game 
waiting to spring forward and consume another line of resources 
dots in the budget maze 
but then he adds at some point it is appropriate to put 
games aside at least for a while at some point there is an 
obligation to be serious 
at some point partisan posturing must yield to the 
responsibility to govern 
darman also weighs in on the current controversy over social 
security funding 
bushs budget proposes no change in either benefits or taxes 
but would use surpluses in the system after the year 1993 when 
the annual budget is required to be balanced under the grammrudman 
law to help pay off the national debt 
by contrast a popular proposal by sen daniel patrick moynihan 
dny would roll back the social security tax increase that took 
effect in january and reduce it further next year 
darman calls the moynihan plan a superficially attractive 
proposal 
but the budget director asserts that in reality cutting the 
social security tax at this time would either force the government 
to raise other taxes to offset the loss in revenues or lead to a 
reduction in benefits 
the presidents proposal is a responsible way to protect 
the future interests of todays workers darman says 
however he concedes social security is a notoriously 
volatile subject when it enters the political domain and whether 
rationality will prevail remains to be determined 
this years budget meets the responsibility to be serious 
darman says in his notcompletelyserious introduction this of 
course is not to assert that the budget will be treated seriously 
in the very next beatthebudget game it is simply to suggest 
that it should be 
