itll be a while before we have any good estimates we still 
cant get into a lot of the places because theyre still flooded 
said red cross disaster director bob hernandez 
all i can tell you is that a lot of people are comparing it to 
1983 which was the worst we ever had and the red cross spent 
125 million in that one he said 
in 83 the amite crested at 405 feet near baton rouge the 
highest crest in 100 years the river crested at 395 feet 
saturday hernandez said 
