opposition groups appealed for negotiations and free elections as a 
solution to ending ethnic tensions 
police used tear gas and truncheons to disperse stonethrowing 
demonstrators in protests that broke out in several kosovo towns 
saturday according to radio belgrade shots may have been fired by 
both sides 
the state tanjug news agency reported several injuries in the 
clashes belgrade radio reported that up to five people may have 
died but the reports could not be confirmed 
protests broke out in the province tuesday on wednesday riot 
police used tear gas and a water cannon to disperse about 40000 
ethnic albanians who demonstrated in pristina the provincial 
capital to protest alleged human rights abuses in kosovo 
