<TEXT>
after eight hours and 2500 miles avianca 
flight 52 fell from the sky but not apparently because of wind 
shear sabotage a collision or any other violent exotic or 
complicated peril of modern aviation 
it may simply have run out of gas 
fuel exhaustion as the experts call it rarely causes airline 
crashes but investigators were trying to determine if that was 
really what sent flight 52 into the long island woods thursday 
night killing 73 passengers and crew members and injuring the 86 
others 
here insofar as it can be determined is what happened 
flight 52 a boeing 707 left el dorado international airport in 
bogota capital city of colombia at 130 pm est after a stop in 
medellin capital city of the cocaine trade the plane headed for 
new york 
the plane according to colombian radio reports had been having 
maintenance problems over the past four months it had been hauled 
back into the shop for repairs 37 times 
it also was heading into rough weather a slowmoving front was 
dumping rain all along the east coast grounding many planes but 
flight 52 was already on its way and its passengers enjoyed a meal 
of chicken and rice and a film starring sean connery 
the travelers included young blanca and pedro beltron who were 
