yes he said but were running out of fuel the tower gave him a 
flight pattern and asked if it was ok ok the captain responded 
the words fuel emergency which might have produced a 
speedier landing plan were never spoken 
the plane swung east out over the atlantic and then north across 
long island part of a great circle that would bring it back to 
kennedy but this maneuver also consumed vast amounts of precious 
fuel at 932 the pilot had more bad news two engines were out 
that was the last the tower heard from flight 52 at 934 it lost 
contact 
in the cockpit the voice recorder stopped the plane began to 
shake the lights inside the cabin went off as did those on the 
wings the only illumination came from emergency lights over the 
doors the passengers were frightened some especially the 
children started to cry or scream 
were descending realized one woman who knew the area but 
theres no airport below 
