all the engines were silent even though the fuel gauges would 
show that the planes tanks still held 1300 gallons 
there had been no explanation from the crew but lozano thought 
he knew the problem were out of fuel 
he said a prayer and lacking a pillow laid his attache case 
over his knees then he bent over in the crash position and waited 
to die five seconds later the dark silent plane hit the tree 
line 
robinson heard something outside a scraping noise like a 
