falling apart 
race saw the kitchen lights flicker switched on his police 
radio and heard a report of a crash he ran out the door 
forgetting to trade his docksiders for boots 
the 707 mowed a path through the trees some 100 feet tall 
before hitting an embankment the right wing broke off and the 
cockpit was crushed everyone and everything was thrown forward 
those in front died faster and in greater numbers 
the plane had crashed onto a steep wooded slope a few feet from 
the deck of a large modern house the captain was dead or dying 
as were the two other officers in the cockpit 
robinson got a flashlight and went out for a look a wire burst 
into flame showing the outline of the plane he could hear a voice 
